you wouldn't read about it
Homonym Number:
Word Class:exclamation
Sense Number:
Definition:expressing a range from chagrin to tolerant surprise that such things could happen: `you wouldn't believe it!'
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: nf P: but used in the Aust Bluey and Curly cartoon strip, 1953 Sep 30 Evening Post (Wellington); AC1950 ca1947 Wellington p.c. R. Mason -->ca1952 Wellington, in a Victoria University English student's essay
